docs.abstract: Silicon Valley has fallen in love with A.I. assistants, but so far they’re hardly impressive. Is it the industry’s fault, or is it ours?
docs.snippet: Silicon Valley has fallen in love with A.I. assistants, but so far they’re hardly impressive. Is it the industry’s fault, or is it ours?
docs.lead_paragraph: Every so often, an idea comes along that mesmerizes Silicon Valley and convinces the most powerful people there that this innovation will irrevocably alter the course of humankind. Outsize proclamations are made, lavish events are held and millions of dollars in venture money are funneled into young, unproven companies. Right now, that fixation has landed on chatbots, little artificial-intelligence programs that work like personalized assistants.

headline.main: What Chatbots Reveal About Our Own Shortcomings
headline.print_headline: What Chatbots Reveal About Our Own Shortcomings

docs.abstract: A deeper reading of recent earnings reports shows an industry in transition, and perhaps getting ready to get even bigger.
docs.snippet: A deeper reading of recent earnings reports shows an industry in transition, and perhaps getting ready to get even bigger.
docs.lead_paragraph: Judging from the way the technology industry hypes itself, tech has a bright future, and always will. This week is a different matter.

headline.main: The No-Good Week in Tech’s (Hopeful) Trip to a Bright Future

docs.abstract: Philanthropic efforts of those who made billions in the tech industry have put the Pacific Northwest at the epicenter of a push to improve global health.
docs.snippet: Philanthropic efforts of those who made billions in the tech industry have put the Pacific Northwest at the epicenter of a push to improve global health.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Inside the factory buildings at Cascade Designs, just south of downtown Seattle, camping and hiking gear for the rugged outdoor life of the Pacific Northwest has been manufactured since the early 1970s. But turn a corner and something new is coming off the shop floor: a compact, no-frills water purifier designed to bring clean water to struggling populations in rural Africa.

headline.main: For Some Top Nonprofits, Changing the World Begins in Seattle
headline.print_headline: From Seattle, With an Eye on the World
